  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/7123580/how-to-convert-a-set-of-integers-to-an-int-array",
  "title" : "How to convert a set of Integers to an int[] array?",
  "body" : "<p>I have no problems converting a <code>Set</code> of strings to a <code>String[]</code> array, but I'm having problems doing so with converting a <code>Set</code> of <code>Integer</code> to an <code>int[]</code> array.</p>\n<p>How can I convert the <code>Integers</code> to its corresponding primitive?</p>\n<p>I cannot seem to find any related questions. Any quick suggestions that can help?</p>\n<p>Sometimes, autoboxing cannot be used, as in the case of arrays. I don't think an array of integers will automatically be converted to an array of ints.</p>\n"
